sentences: Frank Valdor (27 May 1937 – 5 August 2013) was one of the great German bandleaders having sold over 2.5 million records during the 1960s and 1970s.
His album King Size sold 25,000 copies in Finland and was awarded gold status.
Like James Last did Frank Valdor had also a period during the earlier 1970s, when he was a celebrated musician in Scandinavia.
